## [The Async Book](https://doc.rust-lang.org/async-book/)

The official guide to asynchronous programming in Rust. Covers Futures, async/await syntax, and the Tokio runtime in depth.
docs.rust-lang.org
## [Tokio Tutorial](https://tokio.rs/tokio/tutorial)

A hands-on tutorial for learning the Tokio async runtime. Build a key-value store server from scratch using async I/O primitives.
tokio.rs
## [Pin and Suffering](https://fasterthanli.me/articles/pin-and-suffering)

An in-depth exploration of the Pin type in Rust, why it exists, and how it interacts with self-referential async state machines.
fasterthanli.me
## [Futures and Segfaults](https://without.boats/blog/futures-and-segfaults/)

A deep dive into why Rust's Future trait was designed the way it was, focusing on the tradeoffs between convenience and safety.
without.boats
